## LogLayer Project Structure

```
loglayer/
├── docs/                         # Documentation site (vitepress)
│   ├── .vitepress/               # vitepress configuration (including sidebar config)
|   ├── src/                      # Documentation site doc files
│   │   ├── context-managers/     # LogLayer Context manager site docs
|   |   ├── example-integrations/ # Example integrations
|   |   ├── logging-api/          # LogLayer API documentation
|   |   ├── plugins/              # LogLayer Plugin documentation
|   |   ├── transports/           # LogLayer Transports documentation
|   |   ├── mixins/               # LogLayer Mixins documentation
├── packages/
│   ├── core/                     # Core packages
│   │   ├── context-manager/      # Context manager system core
│   │   ├── loglayer/             # Main LogLayer implementation
│   │   ├── plugin/               # Plugin system core
│   │   ├── transport/            # Transport system core
│   │   ├── shared/               # Shared utilities and types
│   │   └── tsconfig/             # Shared TypeScript configurations
│   ├── context-managers/         # Official context manager implementations
│   ├── transports/               # Official transport implementations
│   ├── mixins/                   # Official mixin implementations
│   └── plugins/                  # Official plugins
```

## Common Project Files

For packages in the `packages/` directory, we generally have the following files:

- `biome.json`: Biome configuration file for linting and formatting. The extends path depends on the package location.
- `CHANGELOG.md`: Changelog file (auto-generated) - top header should be the package name.
- `LICENSE`: License file (usually MIT).
- `package.json`: NPM package configuration file.
- `README.md`: Readme file (top header should be the package name).
- `tsconfig.json`: TypeScript configuration file
- `tsdown.config.json`: `tsdown` build configuration file.
- `turbo.json`: Turborepo configuration file, see other packages for examples. 
